</title>
<subSubSection id="EA6DEDC894F9609178D4943B147B75C4" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" type="description">
<paragraph id="F09922B7DCC59729C2F3243781724104" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
Ausdauernd oder 1 
<normalizedToken id="9328D7258DB31D470E8EAA3766597623" originalValue="jährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">jaehrig</normalizedToken>
, aufrecht, kahl. 
<emphasis id="D95983AADE2437494EAB7AB1A6A6D71E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
<normalizedToken id="E0AB8FCAE8A3DEBFBDAE0A93CCA7BF5D" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
eine dichte, 
<normalizedToken id="2D085CB9D474C85577F10FE169B7FCD3" originalValue="ährenartig" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">aehrenartig</normalizedToken>
zusammengezogene, einseitswendige Rispe.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="7CA44A809AC014FF826BB3865C9F86D8" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="0810E8A3DFD829650278B594334D0ACE" originalValue="mehrblütig" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">mehrbluetig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="FA1CC5BB0D50D2B642F58B76A62776E3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
2 verschiedene Typen von 
<normalizedToken id="F6859B93F6DCD45BA25B2DD8DCACA382" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
: sterile 
<normalizedToken id="B97BE7B7D93D363DAC808240C427FC43" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
im untern Teil jedes Rispenastes, fertile 
<normalizedToken id="358D5A936FA92F8572250AAB429B9175" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
an der Spitze jedes Rispenastes;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="1882E9803171561DA786CB99793E4B82" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
meist weniger als 1 mm lang gestielt. Alle Spelzen spitz, Deckspelzen oft aus der Spitze begrannt.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B2BBA6886D5CF463285275C9B1C11D4" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="D33891DFE94F9A199834C3A115C196FF" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cynosurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="798FE6CF70BFB0C128BF6C83EAF92444" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Cynosurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="BACB4127443EA9BCE0144E9124122EC7" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="D2C7131CC287B687B0C5CFA93824B8FC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
5 Arten, die 
<normalizedToken id="2766CEEBFB41596955E8C48D184D832E" originalValue="ursprünglich" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">urspruenglich</normalizedToken>
in den 
<normalizedToken id="F1FA953F3F8FF04ED814BF8855ECD621" originalValue="gemäβigten" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">gemaeβigten</normalizedToken>
Zonen Eurasiens verbreitet sind.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9FC7A9125AF3EF0A8B3BA9C80434330" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
<table id="9F000C31589E76A696376DFA68070D69" frame="void" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" rules="none" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
<tbody id="C3016FD0F1F7D6AAE30239CA70D10F90" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
<tr id="E18232BBE98EE3B37804A884796EDAFC" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
<td id="231EA00F5B796216835D355F2D837BC1" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" valign="top">
1. Grannenartige Spitze der Deckspelzen der fertilen 
<normalizedToken id="48803FAC028CB1F1D28C308AC40CC69E" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
sehr kurz, etwa ⅙ so lang wie die Spelze; 
<normalizedToken id="3AD8F1A64A73E8F9DEF5514A47945590" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
schlank, 5-10 cm lang und bis 1 cm dick; Pflanze ausdauernd
</td>
<td id="6B53F46DC9F309F5D2C3C4238647601C" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="5E250606CB040605C38049A7B1356C94" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cynosurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<italic id="E920BAF7C3B9C835FED4489683556FFD" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">C. cristatus</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="00FD17C7484368028D4D8C6A8238525C" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">
<td id="6BBE74350B6DC3D1FE2DC7758B6BF576" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" valign="top">
1*. Deckspelzen der 
<normalizedToken id="51D9B191F867307A2688D6306B01CC6B" originalValue="fertüen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">fertueen</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="7311D7C24DC89F67BD432F61A8BCCAA2" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
mit langen Grannen (Granne etwa 2mal so lang wie die Spelze); 
<normalizedToken id="B72B3EF5E70598F0A4B7E33312D4F0F0" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
kurz und dick, bis 4 cm lang und bis 1,5 cm dick (ohne Grannen); Pflanze 1 
<normalizedToken id="EDDF860C8EDBACE64205096FCE5107FE" originalValue="jährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">jaehrig</normalizedToken>
</td>
<td id="D4C3B8224A62878D79678562DE732744" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="E5082DE309C6AD60C602943225AC802C" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cynosurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="284" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="echinatus">
<italic id="FE33E97D10DAFC636B0DB09DDC0F852D" pageId="null" pageNumber="284">C. echinatus</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2)
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</paragraph>
